Add fallback definition for TIOCGPTPEER on legacy kernels.

TIOCGPTPEER was introduced in Linux 4.13 for race-free PTY peer opening.
The CoreELEC Amlogic-old kernel (3.14-based backport) does not define
this ioctl, so systemd 257.x fails to compile src/basic/terminal-util.c.

Define the ioctl inline right after the sys/ioctl.h include so the code
paths that use TIOCGPTPEER compile. At runtime the legacy kernel returns
ENOTTY for the ioctl and systemd falls back to the pre-4.13 path
(ptsname + open), which is already present in the same function.

diff --git a/src/basic/terminal-util.c b/src/basic/terminal-util.c
--- a/src/basic/terminal-util.c
+++ b/src/basic/terminal-util.c
@@ -14,5 +14,10 @@
 #include <sys/inotify.h>
 #include <sys/ioctl.h>
+
+#ifndef TIOCGPTPEER
+#define TIOCGPTPEER _IOR('T', 0x41, int)
+#endif
+
 #include <sys/sysmacros.h>
 #include <sys/time.h>
 #include <sys/types.h>
